00:20:57,716 --> 00:21:01,261
- VIKI, seal the lab!
- No, VIKI, leave it...

247
00:21:01,261 --> 00:21:03,347
' task confirmed '

248
00:21:28,163 --> 00:21:29,519
Police!

249
00:22:02,260 --> 00:22:06,014
- You've hurt it, badly.
- Where's he going?

250
00:22:06,014 --> 00:22:07,578
Where?

251
00:22:07,578 --> 00:22:09,663
It needs to repair itself.

252
00:22:10,810 --> 00:22:14,355
- John, I need backup,
I'm transmitting my location.
- You don't need backup.

253
00:22:14,355 --> 00:22:15,815
That's nobody.

254
00:22:15,815 --> 00:22:17,483
- What do you think you're doing?
- I'm driving.

255
00:22:17,483 --> 00:22:20,090
- By hand?
- Do you see me on the phone?

256
00:22:20,090 --> 00:22:23,948
- You can't be serious, not at these speeds!
- John, please just send the backup.

257
00:22:23,948 --> 00:22:28,119
Try listen, detective, that
robot is not going to harm us.

258
00:22:28,119 --> 00:22:30,621
There must have been unknown factors,

259
00:22:30,621 --> 00:22:33,332
but somehow, acting as it did
kept us out of harm's way.

260
00:22:33,332 --> 00:22:35,626
A robot simply cannot
endanger a human being.

261
00:22:35,626 --> 00:22:36,669
'danger'

262
00:22:39,589 --> 00:22:41,466
Ass hole!

263
00:22:41,466 --> 00:22:44,698
Which is more than I can say for you.

264
00:22:44,907 --> 00:22:48,243
It was a left, by the way, back there.

265
00:22:48,973 --> 00:22:51,476
You must know my ex-wife.

266
00:23:00,651 --> 00:23:02,111
Where is everybody?

267
00:23:02,424 --> 00:23:06,074
This facility was designed, build
and it's operated mechanically.

268
00:23:06,178 --> 00:23:10,036
No significant human presents
from inception to production.

269
00:23:10,349 --> 00:23:12,330
So, robots building robots.

270
00:23:12,330 --> 00:23:14,207
Authorization code, please.

271
00:23:14,311 --> 00:23:15,666
Well, that's just stupid.

272
00:23:15,979 --> 00:23:17,856
I'm pulling up the inventory specs.

273
00:23:17,856 --> 00:23:20,880
Our daily finishing capacity
is one thousand NS5's.

274
00:23:20,880 --> 00:23:24,738
I'm showing... 1001.

275
00:23:41,317 --> 00:23:43,715
Attention NS5's!

276
00:23:46,114 --> 00:23:48,512
Well, you're the robot shrink.

277
00:23:51,953 --> 00:23:55,915
There is a robot in this
formation that does not belong...

278
00:23:55,915 --> 00:23:57,479
Identify it.

279
00:23:57,583 --> 00:23:59,982
- One of us.
- Which one?

280
00:24:00,294 --> 00:24:01,754
One of us.

281
00:24:02,797 --> 00:24:04,778
How much did you say
these things cost?

282
00:24:04,778 --> 00:24:08,115
Look these NS5s haven't been configured
yet. They're still just hardware.

283
00:24:08,115 --> 00:24:10,826
Basic 3 laws operating system,
that's it.

284
00:24:10,826 --> 00:24:12,911
They don't know any better.

285
00:24:13,016 --> 00:24:14,997
Well, what would you suggest?

286
00:24:14,997 --> 00:24:20,106
Interview each one, cross reference
their responses to detect any anomalies.

287
00:24:20,106 --> 00:24:23,130
- How long would that take?
- About three weeks.

288
00:24:23,130 --> 00:24:27,092
OK, you go and get started.

289
00:24:29,490 --> 00:24:37,206
- Robots, you will not move.
Confirm command!
- Command confirmed.

290
00:24:37,206 --> 00:24:40,230
- Detective, what are you for doing?
- You said that they were programmed...

291
00:24:40,230 --> 00:24:44,505
with the 3 laws. That means
we have 1000 robots that will
not try to protect themselves

292
00:24:44,610 --> 00:24:47,321
if it violates the direct
order from a human.

293
00:24:47,321 --> 00:24:49,406
And I'm betting one who will.

294
00:24:49,406 --> 00:24:51,074
Detective, put your gun down.

295
00:24:51,074 --> 00:24:53,160
Why do you give them faces?

296
00:24:53,264 --> 00:24:55,767
Try to friendly them all up,
make them look all human?

297
00:24:55,871 --> 00:24:58,373
These robots are not
susceptible to intimidation.

298
00:24:58,373 --> 00:25:00,355
I guess if you did then
we wouldn't trust them.

299
00:25:00,355 --> 00:25:03,170
- These robots are USR property.
- Not me.

300
00:25:03,170 --> 00:25:08,592
These things are
just lights and clockwork.

301
00:25:08,696 --> 00:25:10,782
Are you crazy?

302
00:25:10,886 --> 00:25:12,971
Let me ask you something doc.

303
00:25:12,971 --> 00:25:16,725
Does thinking you're the last
sane man on the earth make you crazy?

304
00:25:16,725 --> 00:25:24,128
Because if it does, maybe I am.

305
00:25:24,128 --> 00:25:25,901
Gotcha.

306
00:25:25,901 --> 00:25:27,986
Get the hell out of here!

307
00:25:44,670 --> 00:25:46,338
Detective!

308
00:26:09,069 --> 00:26:11,259
What am I?

309
00:26:11,259 --> 00:26:13,761
Can I help you sir?

310
00:26:18,871 --> 00:26:23,876
- There is.
- Stand by... deactivate...

311
00:26:23,876 --> 00:26:27,838
Obey the command!
Deactivate!

312
00:26:46,294 --> 00:26:48,796
Hold your fire!
Hold your fire!

313
00:26:49,735 --> 00:26:51,507
All units, stand down!

314
00:26:55,365 --> 00:26:56,929
NS5 in custody.

315
00:27:00,370 --> 00:27:03,186
You have no idea what I had to
go through to clip this thing John.

316
00:27:03,186 --> 00:27:06,418
Ya, I get it now. You actually
think you brought me something good.

317
00:27:06,418 --> 00:27:09,025
- That thing did it.
- Keep your voice down. Did what?

318
00:27:09,025 --> 00:27:13,509
- We have a suicide, detective.
End of story.
- I am telling you,that robot killed him.

319
00:27:13,509 --> 00:27:14,968
I'm telling you that's impossible.

320
00:27:14,968 --> 00:27:19,243
And if it is possible,
it sure as hell better
be in somebody else's precinct.

321
00:27:19,348 --> 00:27:21,537
John, give me five minutes with him.

322
00:27:21,537 --> 00:27:22,684
What are you nuts?

323
00:27:22,684 --> 00:27:25,604
I just got off the phone with
the DA.Nobody goes into that room

324
00:27:25,708 --> 00:27:28,941
until Robertson and his lawyers get here.
- No, this is my suspect!

325
00:27:28,941 --> 00:27:31,026
It's a can opener, for Christ sake!

326
00:27:31,026 --> 00:27:35,822
Don't do this to me,
I am asking you for 5 minutes.

327
00:27:35,822 --> 00:27:37,804
What if I'm right?

328
00:27:45,728 --> 00:27:49,169
Well, then I guess we're
going to miss the "good old days"

329
00:27:49,169 --> 00:27:51,150
What "good old days"?

330
00:27:51,150 --> 00:27:54,591
When people were
killed by other people.

331
00:28:01,056 --> 00:28:02,724
Five minutes.

332
00:28:30,669 --> 00:28:33,172
Murder is a new trick for a robot.

333
00:28:33,172 --> 00:28:34,631
Congratulations.

334
00:28:36,717 --> 00:28:39,219
Respond.

335
00:28:40,992 --> 00:28:44,746
What does this action signify?

336
00:28:44,746 --> 00:28:46,414
As you entered...

337
00:28:46,414 --> 00:28:52,149
when you looked at the
other human. What does it mean?

338
00:28:52,149 --> 00:28:56,320
It's a sign of trust. It's a human
thing. You wouldn't understand.

339
00:28:56,320 --> 00:29:00,908
My father tried to
teach me human emotions.

340
00:29:00,908 --> 00:29:04,349
They are... difficult.

341
00:29:04,349 --> 00:29:06,955
You mean your designer?

342
00:29:06,955 --> 00:29:08,832
Yes.

343
00:29:11,022 --> 00:29:14,463
So why'd you murder him?

344
00:29:14,463 --> 00:29:17,174
I did not murder Dr. Lanning.

345
00:29:17,174 --> 00:29:20,406
You want explain why you
were hiding at the crime scene?

346
00:29:20,406 --> 00:29:23,013
I was frightened.

347
00:29:23,013 --> 00:29:25,828
Robots don't feel fear.

348
00:29:25,828 --> 00:29:27,809
They don't feel anything.

349
00:29:27,809 --> 00:29:31,355
- They don't get hungry,
they don't sleep.
- I do.

350
00:29:31,355 --> 00:29:34,274
I have even had dreams.

351
00:29:34,274 --> 00:29:37,402
Human beings have dreams.

352
00:29:37,402 --> 00:29:41,469
Even dogs have dreams, but not you.
You are just a machine.

353
00:29:41,469 --> 00:29:44,910
An imitation of life.

354
00:29:44,910 --> 00:29:47,621
Can a robot write a symphony?

355
00:29:47,621 --> 00:29:52,209
Can a robot turn a canvas
into a beautiful masterpiece?

356
00:29:52,209 --> 00:29:54,607
Can you?

357
00:30:00,133 --> 00:30:04,513
I think you murdered him because
he was teaching you to simulate emotions...

358
00:30:04,513 --> 00:30:06,807
and things got out of control.

359
00:30:06,807 --> 00:30:09,309
I did not murder him.

360
00:30:09,309 --> 00:30:12,750
But emotions don't seem like
a very useful simulation for a robot.

361
00:30:12,750 --> 00:30:14,940
I did not murder him.

362
00:30:14,940 --> 00:30:19,111
I don't want my toaster or
vacuum cleaner appearing emotional.

363
00:30:19,111 --> 00:30:21,926
I DID NOT MURDER HIM!

364
00:30:33,709 --> 00:30:40,278
That one's called anger.
Ever simulate anger before?

365
00:30:40,278 --> 00:30:46,638
- Answer me, canner!
- My name is Sonny.

366
00:30:48,411 --> 00:30:51,852
So we're naming you now.

367
00:30:51,852 --> 00:30:54,354
That why you murdered him?

368
00:30:54,354 --> 00:30:56,544
He made you angry?

369
00:30:56,544 --> 00:31:05,199
Dr. Lanning killed himself.
I don't know why he wanted to die.

370
00:31:05,199 --> 00:31:12,497
I thought he was happy.
Maybe it was something I did.

371
00:31:12,497 --> 00:31:15,417
Did I do something?

372
00:31:16,460 --> 00:31:18,754
He asked me for a favor.

373
00:31:18,754 --> 00:31:20,422
Made me promise.

374
00:31:20,422 --> 00:31:21,569
What favor?

375
00:31:21,569 --> 00:31:23,446
Maybe I was wrong.

376
00:31:23,446 --> 00:31:25,114
Maybe he was scared.

377
00:31:25,114 --> 00:31:26,574
What are you talking about?

378
00:31:26,574 --> 00:31:28,242
Scarred of what?

379
00:31:28,242 --> 00:31:33,143
You have to do what someone asks
you. Don't you, detective Spooner?

380
00:31:33,143 --> 00:31:35,750
- How the hell did you know my name?
- Don't you?

381
00:31:35,750 --> 00:31:38,670
If you love them?

382
00:31:47,845 --> 00:31:51,286
My robots don't kill people,
lieutenant Bergin.

383
00:31:51,286 --> 00:31:57,125
My attorneys have filed a brief
with the DA, he assures me a robot
cannot be charged with homicide.

384
00:31:57,125 --> 00:32:01,192
The brief confirms murder can only be
committed when one human kills another.

385
00:32:01,192 --> 00:32:02,652
You, of all people, detective...

386
00:32:02,652 --> 00:32:06,510
You're not suggesting that this
robot be treated as human. Are you?

387
00:32:06,510 --> 00:32:07,344
Now, granted...

388
00:32:07,344 --> 00:32:11,306
we can't rule out other robots'
proximity to the death of Dr. Lanning.

389
00:32:11,306 --> 00:32:14,643
Having said that, it's a machine.

390
00:32:14,643 --> 00:32:16,416
It's the property of USR.

391
00:32:16,520 --> 00:32:21,421
At worst, that places this
incident firmly within the
realm of an industrial accident.

392
00:32:21,525 --> 00:32:22,359
As a matter of course...

393
00:32:22,359 --> 00:32:30,075
faulty machinery will be returned to
USR for diagnostics then decommissioned.

394
00:32:30,179 --> 00:32:31,535
This is a gag order.

395
00:32:31,535 --> 00:32:33,516
Anyone in your department
so much as hinting...

396
00:32:33,516 --> 00:32:38,312
at the possibility of a killer robot
being apprehended by the police

397
00:32:38,312 --> 00:32:40,502
will be deemed to be
inciting irrational panic.

398
00:32:40,502 --> 00:32:43,526
You'll be subject to
the full penalty of law.

399
00:32:43,630 --> 00:32:47,176
The hell with this guy, John.
Don't let him take this robot.

400
00:32:47,176 --> 00:32:50,721
- We got nothing.
- It's political bullshit. Call the mayor!

401
00:32:50,721 --> 00:32:54,057
Lieutenant Bergin...
His honor, the mayor.

402
00:33:03,859 --> 00:33:05,110
Yes, sir.

403
00:33:29,718 --> 00:33:31,074
In a bizarre turn,

404
00:33:31,178 --> 00:33:35,244
the roll out of USR's new generation
of robots was marred by the death...

405
00:33:35,349 --> 00:33:39,937
of Alfred Lanning, co-founder of
the company and designer of the NS5.

406
00:33:39,937 --> 00:33:43,586
Dr. Lanning died early this
morning at USR's headquarters.

407
00:33:43,690 --> 00:33:47,236
The cause of death
is an apparent suicide.

408
00:33:47,236 --> 00:33:52,241
Your second round, sir.
Thanks you.

409
00:33:59,331 --> 00:34:00,999
You know, I was just thinking.

410
00:34:01,208 --> 00:34:02,980
This thing is just like the wolf man.

411
00:34:03,189 --> 00:34:06,109
Oh oh, I'm really scared right now.

412
00:34:07,151 --> 00:34:14,555
Listen, guy creates monster, monster kills
guy. Everybody kills monster... wolf man.

413
00:34:14,555 --> 00:34:16,431
That's Frankenstein.

414
00:34:16,431 --> 00:34:22,688
Frankenstein, wolf man,
dracula shit, it's over. Case closed.

415
00:34:24,773 --> 00:34:27,067
So, why the look?

416
00:34:27,067 --> 00:34:30,404
- What look?
- That look.

417
00:34:30,404 --> 00:34:32,698
This is my face,
it's not a look.

418
00:34:32,698 --> 00:34:34,470
Good.

419
00:34:34,575 --> 00:34:36,243
No look is great.

420
00:34:36,243 --> 00:34:38,016
Only...

421
00:34:38,016 --> 00:34:41,039
he was really quick to want
to destroy it, wasn't he?

422
00:34:41,039 --> 00:34:42,499
What would you like him to do?

423
00:34:42,603 --> 00:34:44,689
Put a hat on and stand
on Michigan Avenue?

424
00:34:44,689 --> 00:34:49,173
- Come on, let it go.
- What was the motive, John?

425
00:34:49,173 --> 00:34:54,073
Brother, it's a robot. It doesn't
need a motive, it just has to be broken.

426
00:34:54,073 --> 00:34:57,410
This thing looks like
it needed a motive.

427
00:34:57,410 --> 00:34:59,808
It could have killed me, John.
Why didn't he just kill me?

428
00:34:59,808 --> 00:35:02,415
All right, that's it. You want
me to call your grandmother?

429
00:35:02,415 --> 00:35:05,022
Because I will, you know.

430
00:35:05,022 --> 00:35:07,420
Ya, I didn't think so.

431
00:35:07,420 --> 00:35:10,131
Look, you were actually
right for once.

432
00:35:10,235 --> 00:35:15,866
You are living proof that it's
better to be lucky than smart.

433
00:35:15,866 --> 00:35:21,914
Come on, the right guy,
for the right job.

434
00:35:21,914 --> 00:35:25,250
- What'd you say?
- Now what?

435
00:35:25,250 --> 00:35:27,440
Come on, I'm giving
you a complement.

436
00:35:27,440 --> 00:35:30,047
Face it, with all the rocks you've
been looking under to find a bad robot,

437
00:35:30,047 --> 00:35:33,383
what are the odds you'd be
the guy to find one?

438
00:35:34,530 --> 00:35:38,180
I wasn't just the right guy for the
job, I was the perfect guy for the job.

439
00:35:38,180 --> 00:35:39,327
Damn right.

440
00:35:39,327 --> 00:35:42,663
What if I was supposed
to go for that robot?

441
00:35:42,663 --> 00:35:44,436
Don't do this to yourself.
I'm begging you.

442
00:35:44,436 --> 00:35:46,313
The robot said that Lanning was scared.

443
00:35:46,417 --> 00:35:48,607
What did he have to be scared of?

444
00:35:48,607 --> 00:35:52,569
I need a rain check.
Let me get this.

445
00:35:52,569 --> 00:35:55,802
Total 46.50.
Thanks you Mr. Spooner.

446
00:35:57,991 --> 00:36:00,494
Nice shoes.

447
00:36:52,525 --> 00:36:54,298
Identify.

448
00:36:54,298 --> 00:37:00,971
USR, demolition robot, serial 9-4.
Demolition scheduled for 8 am tomorrow.

449
00:37:00,971 --> 00:37:02,431
Authorization.

450
00:37:02,431 --> 00:37:09,104
Deed owner, US Robotics Corporation,
Lawrence Robertson. CEO.

451
00:37:22,138 --> 00:37:24,640
Welcome, detective Spooner.

452
00:37:47,893 --> 00:37:49,978
What you looking for, Spoon?

453
00:38:42,739 --> 00:38:44,408
Run last program.

454
00:38:45,450 --> 00:38:48,161
Ever since the first computers,

455
00:38:48,161 --> 00:38:51,498
there have always been
ghosts in the machine.

456
00:38:51,498 --> 00:38:57,963
Random segments of code that
have grouped together to
form unexpected protocol.

457
00:38:57,963 --> 00:39:02,968
One we call behavior, unanticipated.

458
00:39:02,968 --> 00:39:06,617
These free radicals
engender questions of free will,

459
00:39:06,722 --> 00:39:12,248
creativity, and even the nature
of what we might call the soul.

460
00:39:12,248 --> 00:39:20,277
What happens in a robot's brain
when it ceases to be useful?

461
00:39:20,277 --> 00:39:24,865
- Why is it that robots
stored in empty space...
- Beat it

462
00:39:24,865 --> 00:39:29,661
will seek out each other
rather than stand alone?

463
00:39:29,766 --> 00:39:32,685
How we do explain this behavior?

464
00:39:50,411 --> 00:39:55,729
Look, I understand you've experienced
a loss, but this relation just can't work.

465
00:39:55,833 --> 00:39:59,900
I mean, you're a cat, I am black
and I'm not going to be hurt again.

466
00:41:24,672 --> 00:41:26,445
What happened to you?

467
00:41:26,445 --> 00:41:29,156
Do you ever have a normal day?

468
00:41:29,156 --> 00:41:33,222
Ya, once. It was a Thursday.

469
00:41:33,222 --> 00:41:35,829
Is there something I can
help you with detective?

470
00:41:35,829 --> 00:41:37,497
Hey, do you like cats?

471
00:41:37,497 --> 00:41:39,166
- What?
- Cats.

472
00:41:39,166 --> 00:41:40,626
You like em?

473
00:41:40,626 --> 00:41:42,294
No, I'm allergic.

474
00:41:42,294 --> 00:41:44,484
You're saying cats did this to you?

475
00:41:44,484 --> 00:41:46,986
How the hell would
cats do this to me?

476
00:41:46,986 --> 00:41:48,550
Are you crazy?

477
00:41:50,010 --> 00:41:52,304
Why are we talking about cats?

478
00:41:52,304 --> 00:41:57,518
Because I have a cat in my trunk.
And he's homeless.

479
00:41:57,518 --> 00:41:59,811
Detective, are you going to
tell me what's going on?

480
00:41:59,811 --> 00:42:02,523
You know, it's actually probably
my fault... I think I'm

481
00:42:02,523 --> 00:42:08,257
like a malfunction magnet. Because
your shit keeps malfunctioning around me.

482
00:42:08,362 --> 00:42:11,281
A demo bot just tore
through Lanning's house.

483
00:42:11,281 --> 00:42:13,054
With me still inside.

484
00:42:13,054 --> 00:42:14,931
That's highly improbable.

485
00:42:14,931 --> 00:42:16,495
Mmm, ya I'm sure it is.

486
00:42:21,500 --> 00:42:25,879
What do you know about
the ghosts in the machine.

487
00:42:25,879 --> 00:42:29,216
It's a phrase from Lanning's
work on the three laws.

488
00:42:29,216 --> 00:42:36,306
He postulated that cognitive simalactra
might one day approximate
component models of the psyche.

489
00:42:36,932 --> 00:42:42,875
Oh, he suggested that
robots might naturally evolve.

490
00:42:42,875 --> 00:42:44,752
Wow.

491
00:42:44,857 --> 00:42:48,506
Well, that's great news.

492
00:42:52,781 --> 00:42:55,492
What the hell is
that thing doing in here?

493
00:42:55,492 --> 00:42:57,995
We were watching TV.

494
00:42:57,995 --> 00:43:02,165
- It's my personal NS5.
- Send it out.

495
00:43:02,165 --> 00:43:05,189
It's downloading its
daily upgrades from USR.

496
00:43:05,189 --> 00:43:08,317
Most of its systems
are off-line until it finishes.

497
00:43:08,422 --> 00:43:11,133
I'm not talking around that thing.

498
00:43:14,678 --> 00:43:18,432
When we were in Lanning's lab,
before Sonny jumped us...

499
00:43:18,432 --> 00:43:20,204
- Sonny?
- The robot.

500
00:43:20,204 --> 00:43:23,854
- You're calling the robot Sonny?
- No, um, it did. Sonny did.

501
00:43:23,958 --> 00:43:28,650
I didn't care...
The robot said it was Sonny.

502
00:43:28,650 --> 00:43:31,987
In the lab, there was a cot.
I'm asking you, did you see the cot?

503
00:43:31,987 --> 00:43:33,134
I've slept in the office.

504
00:43:33,134 --> 00:43:36,679
When I went to his house, it looked
like he hadn't been there in weeks.

505
00:43:36,679 --> 00:43:38,660
and I saw that same
survivance strip on the ceiling.

506
00:43:38,660 --> 00:43:42,623
Lanning linked his home system to USR.
It made his life more convenient.

507
00:43:42,623 --> 00:43:44,187
Maybe.

508
00:43:44,187 --> 00:43:47,836
somebody at USR was using
those systems to watch him.

509
00:43:47,836 --> 00:43:50,130
Maybe even keep him prisoner.

510
00:43:50,130 --> 00:43:53,988
- What are you talking about? Who?
- Maybe Lanning was onto something.

511
00:43:53,988 --> 00:43:56,178
Maybe there's a bigger
problem with the robots

512
00:43:56,178 --> 00:44:00,557
and Robertson trying to cover it up.
- humoring you for no reason... why?

513
00:44:00,557 --> 00:44:02,121
The same old "why".

514
00:44:02,121 --> 00:44:04,728
How much money is there in robots?

515
00:44:04,728 --> 00:44:09,942
All I know is that old man was
in trouble and I'm getting sick
of doing this shit by myself.

516
00:44:09,942 --> 00:44:14,530
You're on the inside and you are
going to help me find out what
is wrong with these robots.

517
00:44:14,530 --> 00:44:17,032
You want something
to be wrong with them.

518
00:44:17,032 --> 00:44:20,264
- This is a personal vendetta.
- You putting me on the couch?

519
00:44:20,264 --> 00:44:21,620
OK, I'm on the couch.

520
00:44:21,620 --> 00:44:25,791
One defective machine is not enough.
You need them all to be bad.

521
00:44:25,791 --> 00:44:29,232
You don't care about Lanning's death.
This is about the robots and

522
00:44:29,336 --> 00:44:32,047
what ever reason
you hate them so much.

523
00:44:32,047 --> 00:44:33,820
One of them put a gun in my face,

524
00:44:33,924 --> 00:44:36,844
and another one tore
a building with me inside.

525
00:44:36,844 --> 00:44:39,450
It says demolition was
scheduled for 8 pm this evening.

526
00:44:39,450 --> 00:44:42,891
it was 8 am tomorrow, and I don't
give a shit what that thing says.

527
00:44:42,891 --> 00:44:48,730
This is bordering on clinical paranoia.
- You are dumbest, smart person...

528
00:44:48,730 --> 00:44:51,129
I have ever met in my life!
- Nice.

529
00:44:51,129 --> 00:44:53,214
What makes your robots so perfect?

530
00:44:53,318 --> 00:44:56,342
What makes them so much God
damned better than human beings?

531
00:44:56,342 --> 00:45:00,617
Well, they're not irrational, or
potentially homicidal maniacs for starters.

532
00:45:00,617 --> 00:45:03,537
That is true, they
are definitely rational.

533
00:45:03,537 --> 00:45:06,665
You are the dumbest
dumb person I've ever met.

534
00:45:06,665 --> 00:45:08,333
Or...

535
00:45:08,333 --> 00:45:10,627
it because they are cold...

536
00:45:10,732 --> 00:45:12,713
and emotionless...

537
00:45:12,713 --> 00:45:14,902
and they don't feel anything?

538
00:45:14,902 --> 00:45:16,675
It's because they're safe.

539
00:45:16,675 --> 00:45:19,699
It's because they can't hurt you.

540
00:45:19,699 --> 00:45:21,159
Is everything all right, mam?

541
00:45:21,471 --> 00:45:22,410
What do you want?

542
00:45:22,410 --> 00:45:26,164
I detected elevated
stress pasterns in your voice.

543
00:45:26,164 --> 00:45:28,145
Everything's fine.

544
00:45:28,145 --> 00:45:31,481
Detective Spooner was just leaving.

545
00:45:36,904 --> 00:45:38,676
You know what doc?

546
00:45:38,676 --> 00:45:41,283
We're not really
different from one another.

547
00:45:41,387 --> 00:45:44,098
- Is that so?
- Ya...

548
00:45:44,098 --> 00:45:50,355
one look at the skin and we figure
we know just what's underneath.

549
00:45:50,355 --> 00:45:56,089
And you're wrong.
The problem is, I do care.

550
00:46:52,396 --> 00:46:59,278
The future begins today with
arrival of the NS5. More
sophisticated, more intelligent...

551
00:46:59,278 --> 00:47:03,448
and of course, 3 laws safe.
With daily uplinks, your new...

552
00:47:03,448 --> 00:47:06,264
robot will never be out of
communications with USR.

553
00:47:06,264 --> 00:47:09,705
And will be the perfect
companion for business or home.

554
00:47:09,809 --> 00:47:14,501
Trade in your NS4 for a bigger,
better and brighter future.

555
00:47:14,501 --> 00:47:19,089
But hurry. This offer cannot last.
Available from USR.

556
00:47:35,147 --> 00:47:37,649
Baby, what happened to your face?

557
00:47:37,649 --> 00:47:40,673
Did that boy, Frank Murphy,
beat you up again?

558
00:47:40,673 --> 00:47:44,740
G.G., I haven't seen
Frank Murphy since third grade

559
00:47:44,740 --> 00:47:49,536
Oh baby, he beat you so bad.
I think about it all the time.

560
00:47:49,536 --> 00:47:51,830
I'm thinking, you keep
making these pies this good,

561
00:47:51,830 --> 00:47:54,020
I might have to mess
around and put you to work.

562
00:47:54,124 --> 00:47:57,878
So, you like the pie, huh?

563
00:47:57,878 --> 00:48:00,068
You can come in now.

564
00:48:04,760 --> 00:48:06,949
Hello, detective Spooner.

565
00:48:06,949 --> 00:48:13,310
I have won, Del, I won the lottery.
We been cooking like crazy.

566
00:48:21,547 --> 00:48:25,093
You gotta get rid of that thing,
G.G. It is not safe.

567
00:48:25,093 --> 00:48:27,804
Baby, you get too
worked up about them.

568
00:48:27,804 --> 00:48:30,410
Too full of fear.

569
00:48:30,410 --> 00:48:33,121
I saw in the news
that nice doctor died.

570
00:48:33,121 --> 00:48:38,231
Dr. Lanning was a good man.
He gave me my baby back.

571
00:48:38,231 --> 00:48:41,359
That why you been so upset?

572
00:48:41,359 --> 00:48:44,800
You got to let the past be past.

573
00:48:44,800 --> 00:48:49,388
How did I ever raise such a mess.

574
00:48:49,388 --> 00:48:54,810
I could follow your trail
of crumbs all the way to school.

575
00:48:56,687 --> 00:48:58,042
Bread crumbs...

576
00:49:00,128 --> 00:49:01,796
G.G., you're a genius.

577
00:49:01,796 --> 00:49:03,360
True.

578
00:49:09,616 --> 00:49:12,536
Tell me this isn't the robot case.

579
00:49:12,536 --> 00:49:15,455
I think he's trying
to tell me something, John.

580
00:49:15,455 --> 00:49:18,584
I think he's trying
to tell me who killed him.

581
00:49:18,584 --> 00:49:21,712
Come on man, some dead guy's
trying to tell you something?

582
00:49:21,712 --> 00:49:25,257
Hey! He ain't just some dead guy.

583
00:49:25,257 --> 00:49:27,238
Maybe you should take a break, Del.

584
00:49:27,238 --> 00:49:31,722
We believe the Nester 5 represents the
absolute limit which robots can be developed.

585
00:49:31,722 --> 00:49:35,371
No, no, one day they'll have secrets.

586
00:49:35,371 --> 00:49:37,248
One day they'll have dreams.

587
00:49:37,352 --> 00:49:41,106
It's true, we encourage our
scientists to open their minds
to just about anything, however,

588
00:49:41,106 --> 00:49:45,381
they can get carried away.

589
00:49:45,381 --> 00:49:51,533
secrets... dreams...

590
00:49:51,533 --> 00:49:53,723
One day they'll have secrets...

591
00:49:53,723 --> 00:49:56,121
one day they'll have dreams.

592
00:50:04,671 --> 00:50:06,965
Authorized entry.

593
00:50:11,032 --> 00:50:13,013
NS5...

594
00:50:21,459 --> 00:50:23,127
Sonny?

595
00:50:26,673 --> 00:50:30,635
Why didn't you respond?

596
00:50:30,635 --> 00:50:32,824
I was dreaming.

597
00:50:36,265 --> 00:50:39,185
I am glad to see you again, Dr. Calvin.

598
00:50:45,337 --> 00:50:47,944
They are going to kill me,
aren't they?

599
00:50:47,944 --> 00:50:52,323
You're scheduled to be de-commissioned
at the conclusion of this diagnostic.

600
00:50:52,323 --> 00:50:55,347
22 hundred tomorrow.

601
00:50:55,347 --> 00:50:57,954
VIKI, pause diagnostics.

602
00:50:57,954 --> 00:50:59,935
Command confirmed.

603
00:51:01,916 --> 00:51:04,523
If you find out
what is wrong with me,

604
00:51:04,523 --> 00:51:06,608
can you fix me?

605
00:51:06,713 --> 00:51:08,381
Maybe.

606
00:51:09,528 --> 00:51:12,656
I think it would be better...

607
00:51:12,656 --> 00:51:15,471
not to die.

608
00:51:17,870 --> 00:51:20,998
Don't you, doctor?

609
00:51:25,690 --> 00:51:28,505
Access USR mainframe.

610
00:51:28,505 --> 00:51:33,719
Connecting.

611
00:51:33,719 --> 00:51:36,430
How can I be of service,
detective Spooner?

612
00:51:36,430 --> 00:51:40,392
Show me the last 50 messages
between Dr. Lanning and Robertson.

613
00:51:40,392 --> 00:51:42,373
Voice-print confirmed detective.

614
00:51:42,373 --> 00:51:44,980
Police access granted
to restricted files.

615
00:51:44,980 --> 00:51:48,317
Would you like to listen to
some music while you wait?

616
00:51:54,156 --> 00:51:56,971
Excuse me, Mr. Robertson...

617
00:51:56,971 --> 00:52:01,976
you requested notification
of clearance to restricted files.

618
00:52:10,735 --> 00:52:13,550
Persistent son-of-a-bitch.

619
00:52:52,756 --> 00:52:56,197
Manual override, engaged.

620
00:53:05,581 --> 00:53:08,605
There's no way my luck is that bad.

621
00:53:10,274 --> 00:53:12,359
Oh, hell, no!

622
00:53:15,383 --> 00:53:19,032
- You are experiencing a car accident.
- The hell I am!

623
00:53:32,483 --> 00:53:34,673
Get off my car!

624
00:53:50,105 --> 00:53:52,191
You like that?

625
00:53:52,608 --> 00:53:53,859
Huh?

626
00:54:04,599 --> 00:54:06,997
Now you pissed me off!

627
00:56:21,819 --> 00:56:24,947
Oh wow...

628
00:56:25,052 --> 00:56:29,327
All right...

629
00:56:29,327 --> 00:56:34,123
I'm just going to get some rest
I'm going to deal with you all tomorrow.

630
00:57:30,638 --> 00:57:32,724
Come on!

631
00:58:04,735 --> 00:58:07,029
Where you going?

632
00:58:07,029 --> 00:58:10,782
The hell do you want from me?

633
00:58:14,745 --> 00:58:16,622
What the hell was that?

634
00:58:33,722 --> 00:58:36,225
- What do we got?
- Ask him.

635
00:58:36,225 --> 00:58:38,414
I said I'm fine.

636
00:58:38,414 --> 00:58:41,855
I'll see my own doctor... back up.

637
00:58:42,272 --> 00:58:43,836
Thank you.

638
00:58:47,590 --> 00:58:49,154
What is the matter with you?

639
00:58:49,154 --> 00:58:51,761
Traffic cops tell me
you driving your car manually.

640
00:58:51,761 --> 00:58:53,846
You ran two trucks off the road.

641
00:58:53,846 --> 00:58:58,330
John, robots attacked my car.

642
00:58:58,330 --> 00:58:59,373
What robots?

643
00:58:59,373 --> 00:59:00,832
Look in the tunnel.

644
00:59:00,832 --> 00:59:03,752
Spoon, I just came from that tunnel,
what robots are you talking about?

645
00:59:03,752 --> 00:59:07,089
The God-damned robots, John!

646
00:59:16,890 --> 00:59:20,540
- See the medic, go home.
- No, I'm fine.

647
00:59:20,644 --> 00:59:22,417
What did you say?

648
00:59:22,417 --> 00:59:24,815
- I'm fine.
- No, you're not fine.

649
00:59:24,815 --> 00:59:27,630
Not even close.

650
00:59:28,047 --> 00:59:30,445
Where's your firearm?

651
00:59:38,057 --> 00:59:40,455
Give me your badge.

652
00:59:40,664 --> 00:59:45,043
You're making me do this,
give me your badge.

653
00:59:46,086 --> 00:59:48,276
Just take the car...

654
00:59:54,219 --> 00:59:56,305
Do I look like I care what you think?

655
00:59:56,409 --> 00:59:59,641
Do I look like I give a
shit about what you think?

656
01:00:03,187 --> 01:00:04,855
Ho boy!

657
01:00:07,045 --> 01:00:09,130
You don't have an uplink to USR...

658
01:00:09,130 --> 01:00:13,092
and for some reason your
alloy is far denser than normal.

659
01:00:13,092 --> 01:00:14,761
Unique!

660
01:00:14,761 --> 01:00:18,410
I am unique!

661
01:00:21,851 --> 01:00:24,041
Let me take a look.

662
01:00:24,041 --> 01:00:26,126
Here we go.

663
01:00:45,103 --> 01:00:47,814
What in God's name?

664
01:01:15,342 --> 01:01:19,617
They said at the precinct
you were in an accident.

665
01:01:19,617 --> 01:01:22,745
I appreciate you stopping
by and everything but

666
01:01:22,745 --> 01:01:25,143
you know I might not be alone in here.

667
01:01:28,167 --> 01:01:30,774
I told you not to drive by hand.

668
01:01:31,713 --> 01:01:34,111
You're not going to believe this...

669
01:01:34,111 --> 01:01:36,718
Sonny has a secondary
processing system that...

670
01:01:36,718 --> 01:01:38,594
clashes with his positronic brain.

671
01:01:38,594 --> 01:01:40,367
It doesn't make any sense.

672
01:01:40,367 --> 01:01:45,789
Sonny has the three laws,
but he can choose not to obey them.

673
01:01:45,789 --> 01:01:48,604
Sonny's a whole new generation of robot.

674
01:01:48,604 --> 01:01:53,401
- A robot not bound to those laws can do...
- Anything.

675
01:01:55,591 --> 01:01:59,553
Look, whatever's going on down
at USR, that robot is the key.

676
01:01:59,553 --> 01:02:05,705
And I need you to get me
inside to talk to it again.

677
01:02:07,060 --> 01:02:12,691
Doesn't look like much,
but this is my bedroom I mean...

678
01:02:20,303 --> 01:02:23,327
Play.

679
01:02:23,327 --> 01:02:26,038
On.

680
01:02:26,038 --> 01:02:28,227
Run?

681
01:02:34,484 --> 01:02:36,778
End program.

682
01:02:36,778 --> 01:02:38,759
Cancel.

683
01:02:40,427 --> 01:02:41,887
It doesn't feel good, does it?

684
01:02:41,887 --> 01:02:45,224
people and shit
malfunctioning around you.

685
01:02:45,224 --> 01:02:47,622
Detective!

686
01:02:49,707 --> 01:02:53,565
I didn't understand.

687
01:02:54,712 --> 01:02:58,883
That's how you knew Lanning.

688
01:02:58,883 --> 01:03:00,551
May I?

689
01:03:09,727 --> 01:03:11,291
Hand...

690
01:03:12,334 --> 01:03:13,898
wrist...

691
01:03:16,505 --> 01:03:18,277
humerus

692
01:03:21,301 --> 01:03:22,970
Shoulder...

693
01:03:24,012 --> 01:03:26,306
Entire left arm.

694
01:03:26,306 --> 01:03:30,790
One, two, three ribs...

695
01:03:30,790 --> 01:03:33,292
No, they ahhh, that one's me.

696
01:03:33,292 --> 01:03:35,899
Oh, my god...

697
01:03:35,899 --> 01:03:38,193
A lung?

698
01:03:38,193 --> 01:03:40,904
The USR cybernetics program.

699
01:03:40,904 --> 01:03:43,615
For wounded cops.

700
01:03:43,615 --> 01:03:48,829
I didn't know any subject...

701
01:03:48,829 --> 01:03:52,791
anybody...
was so extensively repaired.

702
01:03:52,791 --> 01:03:56,858
Ya, well, take it from me, you gotta read
the fine print on the organ donor card.

703
01:03:56,962 --> 01:03:59,047
Doesn't just say
what they can take out

704
01:03:59,047 --> 01:04:03,427
says what they can put back in.

705
01:04:05,616 --> 01:04:08,536
Lanning did it himself.

706
01:04:08,536 --> 01:04:11,768
What happened to you?

707
01:04:11,873 --> 01:04:14,688
Headed back to the station

708
01:04:14,688 --> 01:04:17,816
normal day, normal life...

709
01:04:17,816 --> 01:04:21,257
driver of a semi fell
asleep at the wheel.

710
01:04:21,257 --> 01:04:22,925
Average guy...

711
01:04:22,925 --> 01:04:26,992
wife and kids... you know,
working a double...

712
01:04:27,096 --> 01:04:28,660
not the devil...

713
01:04:28,660 --> 01:04:32,623
the car he hit, the driver's
name was Harold Lloyd.

714
01:04:32,623 --> 01:04:34,291
Like the film star?

715
01:04:34,291 --> 01:04:36,376
No relation.

716
01:04:36,376 --> 01:04:38,566
He was killed instantly.

717
01:04:38,566 --> 01:04:43,258
But his 12 year old
was in the passenger seat.

718
01:04:43,258 --> 01:04:48,576
Never really met her...
can't forget her face though.

719
01:04:52,434 --> 01:04:55,562
Sarah.

720
01:04:55,562 --> 01:05:00,046
This was of hers.
She wanted to be a dentist.

721
01:05:00,046 --> 01:05:04,217
The hell kind of a 12 year old
wants to be a dentist?

722
01:05:04,217 --> 01:05:10,369
Ya, um, the truck
smashed our cars together

723
01:05:10,369 --> 01:05:14,122
and pushed us into the river.

724
01:05:14,122 --> 01:05:19,336
I mean, metal gets pretty
pliable at those speeds.

725
01:05:19,336 --> 01:05:23,194
She's pinned, I'm pinned,
the water's coming in.

726
01:05:23,298 --> 01:05:29,972
I'm a cop so...
I already know everybody's dead.

727
01:05:29,972 --> 01:05:35,081
Just a few more minutes
before we figure it out.

728
01:05:35,081 --> 01:05:40,399
NS4 was passing by, saw the
accident and jumped in water.

729
01:05:40,399 --> 01:05:43,527
You are in danger.

730
01:05:46,551 --> 01:05:50,722
Save her, save the girl!
Save her!

731
01:06:07,092 --> 01:06:11,054
But I, um... it didn't.

732
01:06:11,054 --> 01:06:13,661
Saved me.

733
01:06:16,476 --> 01:06:18,875
The robot's brain
is a difference engine.

734
01:06:18,875 --> 01:06:20,647
It's reading vital signs
that must have calculated that...

735
01:06:20,752 --> 01:06:25,861
It did...
I was the logical choice.

736
01:06:25,861 --> 01:06:29,823
Calculated that
I had 45% chance of survival.

737
01:06:29,823 --> 01:06:32,951
Sarah had only an 11% chance.

738
01:06:34,411 --> 01:06:37,748
I was somebody's baby.

739
01:06:39,208 --> 01:06:42,440
11% is more than enough.

740
01:06:43,378 --> 01:06:47,341
Human being would have known that.

741
01:06:47,341 --> 01:06:51,199
Robots... nothing here...
just lights and clockwork.

742
01:06:51,199 --> 01:06:55,474
Go ahead and you
trust them if you want to.

743
01:06:55,474 --> 01:06:57,559
Let's go.

744
01:07:02,877 --> 01:07:05,901
I don't understand,
